## Workshops

Hey {{ first name }},

Welcome to the PyCon India 2020 Workshops. Thank you for choosing to attend our workshops for getting hands-on knowledge about things you've been looking to learn.

The workshops will be taking place on Hopin, which you can join using < >, and you can interact with other attendees and speakers on our Zulip channel [this.](https://pyconindia.zulipchat.com/join/it6vi5wfhfbdwr4kcn5mwa6c/)

We will be having 2 sessions of workshops, with 4 parallel workshops in each session. You are free to join any workshop at any time you feel comfortable. The updated schedule for the workshops will available in the Hopin event, and we will be staring with the first session at 11:30 IST (UTC+5:30).

Here is a list of all the available workshops which you can join:

- [Getting Started with Python](https://in.pycon.org/cfp/2020/proposals/getting-started-with-python~b4x8V/) Evan Smith
- [Python for Computational Social Science with Text, Networks, and clever data games](https://in.pycon.org/cfp/2020/proposals/python-for-computational-social-science-with-text-networks-and-clever-data-games~dyPPE/) Bhargav Srinivasa
- [Creating real-world simulations using Numpy, SciPy, and Matplotlib](https://in.pycon.org/cfp/2020/proposals/creating-real-world-simulations-using-numpy-scipy-and-matplotlib~e0Rgy/) Ashok Govindarajan
- [Hands-On: Containerizing Python and Deploying to IoT and Edge Devices](https://in.pycon.org/cfp/2020/proposals/hands-on-containerizing-python-and-deploying-to-iot-and-edge-devices~egJYk/) David T & Vipul Gupta
- [Python on Kubernetes: A primer](https://in.pycon.org/cfp/2020/proposals/python-on-kubernetes-a-primer~aOY7Y/) Nabarun Pal
- [Animating Data in PowerPoint](https://in.pycon.org/cfp/2020/proposals/animating-data-in-powerpoint~dyR6e/) Anand S
- [Concurrency Patterns with Python](https://in.pycon.org/cfp/2020/proposals/concurrency-patterns-with-python~e9r8B/) Anmol Jindal

Please make sure you have set up your system correctly with the prerequisites provided in the workshop description.

We hope you have a fun learning experience at the workshops. If you have any problems or queries during the workshops, please reach out to the Help Desk on [Zulip](https://pyconindia.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/258750-2020.2Fhelpdesk) or Hopin.

Please make sure you follow the conference [Code of Conduct](https://in.pycon.org/2020/coc/) to make the conference a great experience for everyone.

Regards,

PyCon India 2020 Team
